java.lang.Object

      de.uni.bamberg.wiai.minf.forflow.datagenerator.controller.datageneration.filltype.Name
All Implemented Interfaces:
FillBehaviour, ObservableFillBehaviour, ObservableGenerator, java.lang.Cloneable
public class Name
extends Generator

This generator is responsible for creating names. It is different from FirstName and LastName in that way, that it combines both in once generator. That means, for an attribute a prename and a surname are generated. It's possible to choose between language dependent names, like for US or German. This class inherits also behaviour from Generator.

Observable
Notice, the class implements FillBehaviour interface. It makes this kind of strategy observable. Observable means in this context, whenever an observer registers to or un-registers from this class, the subject itself notifies the UI to register this class in a specific list of generators.

getValueAt

public final java.lang.String getValueAt(int n)
Description copied from interface: FillBehaviour
this method has the job of retrieving the value at the specified index. Most fill behaviour strategies are based on value files. These files have a specific amount of possible values from i = 1, ..., n where i is the index. When the process of generating test data is activated, to each facet values of the fill behaviour are used. To get values in the range of the value file, this method is needed. By the way, only the strategies itselves have access to value files.

Specified by:

Specified by:

the value at position n or null

setSex

public void setSex(SexType sex)
to generate accurate prenames, the generator needs to know which sex type it is. It doesn't make sense to generate a prename for girls if the sex type is male and vice versa.

The default gender is set to female.

Parameters:
sex - which sex type is it? male or female

getSex

public final SexType getSex()
gets the sex type for this generator. It's important to distinguish between female and male types, because it doesn't make sense to generate a prename for girls when it's a male.

The default setting is female.

getN2

public final int getN2()
gets the additional N also called N2. Remember, this is the name object and each name consists of a first name and a last name. If you wanna generate only one of them use FirstName or LastName instead.

The total amount returned here is valid for the part 'last name'. If you wanna get N1 use Generator.getN() instead. It gives you N for prenames.

Returns:
N2 = Σn_i

notifyObserverGenerator

public void notifyObserverGenerator(boolean add)
Description copied from interface: ObservableGenerator
Here's the fun part; this is where we tell all observers about the state. Because they are all Observers, we know how to notify them.

This observable is different from common usage, we notify about operations to use, rather updating data structure.

Parameters:
add - here is the operation. There is one of two operations possible.
  • add
    • This operation is explicit, if the flag is set to true. This registers the observable to a list holding available generators.
  • remove
    • This operation is implicit, if the flag is set to false. This is the vice versa function. It removes the subject from the list of available generators.
